-- Nigeria’s Ruling Party Names Bamanga Tukur as Chairman
-- B y   M a r a m   M a z e n
-- 2012-03-24T17:25:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-24/nigeria-s-ruling-party-names-bamanga-tukur-as-chairman.html
Bamanga Tukur was elected as the
new chairman of  Nigeria ’s ruling  People’s Democratic Party  for
the next four years.  Tukur, who’s from the northeastern Adamawa state, won as
ten other candidates pulled out, Defense Minister  Bello Haliru
Mohammed  said today at a party convention in Abuja, the
country’s capital.  The PDP, formed in 1998 following the death of military
ruler Sani Abacha, has been in power since 1999. The convention
was also attended by Nigeria’s President  Goodluck Jonathan . The
PDP said 3,185 delegates voted for Tukur, 12 voted against him
and 51 votes were invalid.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Maram Mazen in Abuja at 
